Casualty insurance reserves relating to the Company's retention programs are based on undiscounted actuarial estimates. These estimates are based on historical information and on certain assumptions about future events. Changes in assumptions for such factors as medical costs and legal actions, as well as changes in actual experience, could cause these estimates to change in the near term. The Company generally receives estimates of outstanding casualty insurance exposures from its independent actuary twice per year and differences between these estimated actuarial exposures and the Company&#8217;s recorded amounts are adjusted as appropriate. The Company had reserves for these programs of $ 57.6 million and $ 56.5 million as of January 1, 2023 and January 2, 2022, respectively. 

